html:
http://ifttt.com/terms
Any comments, suggestions, or feedback relating to the Site or the Service (collectively "Feedback") submitted to IFTTT shall become the property of IFTTT or its designee. IFTTT will not be required to treat any Feedback as confidential, and will not be liable for any ideas (including without limitation, product, Site, Service or advertising ideas) and will not incur any liability as a result of any similarities that may appear in our future Site, Service, or operations.

I'm not sure it's bad or neutral. It needs to claim property to be able to use feedback in order to use it to improve its service, otherwise it would be futile. It might be bad since feedback is a user generated content and the user might feel fair to keep the intellectual property or prefer to keep it confidential.

--
